00:05:58.830 --> 00:06:01.090
Let's say it's 10 kilograms.
Let's say I have

00:06:01.090 --> 00:06:05.490
a 10-kilogram mass.

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:09.590
And I want to place it some
distance d from the fulcrum or

00:06:09.590 --> 00:06:12.600
from the axis of rotation so
that it completely balances

00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:14.140
this 5-kilogram mass.

00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:17.550
So how far from the axis of
rotation do I put this

00:06:17.550 --> 00:06:19.390
10-kilogram mass?

00:06:19.390 --> 00:06:20.310
This is the distance, right?

00:06:20.310 --> 00:06:21.270
Because we actually carry
the distance to the

00:06:21.270 --> 00:06:22.720
