00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:25.750
Well, how much force
is this 10-kilogram

00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:27.400
mass exerting downwards?

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:30.120
Well, it's 10 kilograms times 10
meters per second squared,

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:34.620
it's 100 Newtons.

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:35.540
This is acting what?

00:06:35.540 --> 00:06:37.390
This is acting clockwise,
right?

00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:39.830
This one's acting clockwise
and this one's acting

00:06:39.830 --> 00:06:41.130
counterclockwise, right?

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:42.750
So they are offsetting
each other.

00:06:42.750 --> 00:06:43.840
So we could do it a
couple of ways.

00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:50.190
We could say that 50 Newtons,
the moment in the

00:06:50.190 --> 00:06:54.950
counterclockwise direction, 50
Newtons times 10 meters, in

00:06:54.950 --> 00:06:57.890
order for this thing to not
rotate has to be equal to the

00:06:57.890 --> 00:07:00.560
moment in the clockwise
direction.

00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:02.520
And so the moment in the
clockwise direction is equal

00:07:02.520 --> 00:07:12.140
to 100 Newtons times some
distance, let's call that d,

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:14.230
100 Newtons times d, and
then we could just

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:15.210
solve for d, right?

00:07:15.210 --> 00:07:18.650
We get 50 times 10 is 500.

00:07:18.650 --> 00:07:24.730
500 Newton-meters is equal
to 100 Newtons times d.

00:07:24.730 --> 00:07:25.740
That's 100.

00:07:25.740 --> 00:07:29.970
Divide both sides by 100, you
get 5 meters is equal to d.

00:07:29.970 --> 00:07:32.410
So d is equal to 5.

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:33.420
That's interesting.

00:07:33.420 --> 00:07:35.950
And I think this kind of
confirms your intuition from

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:40.390
